As Rv is decreased from 50,000 ohms to 46,000 ohms, the circuit goes from a limit cycle through a period doubling to a one-well chaotic attractor to a two-well chaotic attractor. With Rv held constant the transmitter 800 and receiver 900 can produce a number of synchronized signals with the output SB" of the element B" being used to confirm synchronicity as previously discussed. If Rv is varied information can be transferred as will be discussed in detail with respect to FIGS. 20-27.
